what is a variable?
variable is like a container that holds data. Very similar to how our containers in kitchen holds sugar, salt etc Creating a variable is like creating a placeholder in memory and assigning it some value. In python its as easy as writing.

a=2
b = true
c = "Akshay"
d = None


List is Mutable.
Tuples are Immutable(You cannot change the content, It is fixed)
For Set--> curly braces.
Dictionary --> Curly braces
{} , dict()--> Empty dictionary
set() --> Dictionary is a common datatypes that we are going to use in our daily life.


IDENTIFIER:
Any name in python program is nothig but an Identifier.\
It can be class name,function or variable name.
Ex: student_roll=10